description: From Latin strepent, from strepere (“to noise”); compare obstreperous.

adjectives.description: strepent (comparative more strepent, superlative most strepent)

examples: Peace to the ſtrepent horn ! / Let no harſh diſſonance diſturb the morn, / No ſounds inelegant and rude / Her ſacred ſolitudes profane !
